==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Idealist
<hw>I*de"al*ist</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>id⟦eacute⟧aliste</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One who idealizes;
one who forms picturesque fancies; one given to romantic
expectations.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>One who holds the doctrine of idealism, in any
sense. In senses 4 and 5 of <er>idealism</er>, opposed to
<contr>realist</contr>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Idealistic</ent>⟦br⟧
